DNA analysis of the bones of ‘Altamura Man’ was found in a cave in Altamura, Italy has revealed he was a Neanderthal who fell into the cave 128,000 to 187,000 years ago . 
  He is thought to have starved to death after falling down a sinkhole . 
  The bones were found fused to the walls of the cave in Lamalunga . 
  DNA extracted from the bones is the oldest to ever be extracted from a human . 
  It was found he was an adult male who died in the cave . 
 